<p>I'm having trouble with this program that is supposed to ask the user for an input in order to solve the area and perimeter of a few geometric figures.</p>  <p>What I'm trying to do, is make this program to ask for every input it needs, rather than me declaring it right away in the code.</p>  <p>So, how can I make that happen? I already tried using scanner, but it gives me an error, either on the main class or the methods.</p>  <pre><code>package figgeo;  public class FigGeo {        public static void main(String[] args) {          Circulo circuloEntero = new Circulo(4);         Circulo circuloReal = new Circulo(5.6);         circuloEntero.imprimir();         circuloReal.imprimir();          Cuadrado cuadradoEntero = new Cuadrado(21);         Cuadrado cuadradoReal = new Cuadrado(12.7);         cuadradoEntero.imprimir();         cuadradoReal.imprimir();          Rectangulo rectanguloEntero = new Rectangulo(6, 7);         Rectangulo rectanguloReal = new Rectangulo(3.5, 4.4);         rectanguloEntero.imprimir();         rectanguloReal.imprimir();          Trapecio trapecioEntero = new Trapecio(11, 6, 4);         Trapecio trapecioReal = new Trapecio(11.1, 6.1, 4.1);         trapecioEntero.imprimir();         trapecioReal.imprimir();          TrianguloEquilatero equilateroEntero = new TrianguloEquilatero(6);         TrianguloEquilatero equilateroReal = new TrianguloEquilatero(6.5);         equilateroEntero.imprimir();         equilateroReal.imprimir();          }  } </code></pre>  <p>That's my main class. Then here's one example of one of my method classes which I'm overloading:</p>  <pre><code>/*  * To change this license header, choose License Headers in Project Properties.  * To change this template file, choose Tools | Templates  * and open the template in the editor.  */ package figgeo;  /**  *  * @author Joaqu√≠n  */ public class Trapecio {      private int baseMayorEntera, baseMenorEntera, alturaEntera;     private double baseMayorReal, baseMenorReal, alturaRe